message.content:
Sure! Here is a sample meal plan for the week:

Breakfast:
- Oatmeal with berries and almond milk
- Scrambled eggs with spinach and tomatoes
- Greek yogurt with banana slices and granola

Lunch:
- Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, and balsamic vinaigrette dressing
- Tuna salad with mixed greens and whole grain crackers
- Quinoa bowl with black beans, roasted vegetables (such as bell peppers, zucchini, and carrots), avocado, and lime juice

Dinner:
- Grilled salmon with roasted sweet potatoes and steamed broccoli
- Stir-fry with tofu, mixed vegetables (such as bell peppers, onions, and snow peas), and brown rice
- Chicken stir-fry with mixed vegetables (such as bell peppers, onions, and snow peas) and brown rice

Snacks:
- Apples with almond butter
- Roasted chickpeas
- Carrot sticks with hummus
- Hard-boiled eggs

Remember to adjust the portions according to your calorie needs and preferences. Enjoy your healthy meal plan!
